## Week 3 Deliverables

---

## 1. User Personas

### Elderly Patient
- Needs simple reminders  
- Prefers easy and clear interface  
- Struggles with complex apps  

### Busy Professional
- Needs quick notifications  
- Has a busy schedule  
- Wants minimal interaction  

### Caregiver
- Monitors patient medication  
- Helps manage schedules  
- Needs tracking system  

---

## 2. Functional Requirements
- Users can register and log in  
- Users can add, edit, and delete medications  
- Users can set time and dosage for each medicine  
- System sends reminder notifications  
- Users can mark medicine as taken or missed  
- System displays daily schedule in dashboard  
- System stores medication history  

---

## 3. Non-Functional Requirements
- Easy-to-use interface (especially for elderly users)  
- Fast performance and quick response time  
- Secure storage of user data  
- High availability (accessible anytime)  
- Scalable for future improvements  

---

## 4. User Stories
- As a user, I want to add my medicines so I can manage them easily  
- As a user, I want to receive reminders so I don’t forget my doses  
- As a user, I want to track taken or missed medicine  
- As a caregiver, I want to monitor patient medication  

---

## 5. Acceptance Criteria
- Medicine can be added with correct details  
- Notifications are triggered at the correct time  
- Users can update medicine status (taken/missed)  
- Dashboard shows accurate daily schedule  
- Data is saved and can be retrieved anytime 
